1
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:34,708
[KYON] Something's wrong...
That's what it felt like anyway.

2
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,583
[KYON] I didn't care about
the baseball game on TV

3
00:00:38,666 --> 00:00:40,958
because it was between
schools from another town.

4
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:43,000
But, because I tend to
symphatize with underdogs,

5
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:45,416
I ended up rooting
for the losing team.

6
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,833
And it was right about then,

7
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:51,166
that I suddenly got the
feeling Haruhi was gonna call.

8
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:52,666
[phone rings]

9
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,583
Your phone's ringing, Kyon.

10
00:00:54,666 --> 00:00:56,833
I know; you don't
have to tell me.

11
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:00,625
[HARUHI]
Hey, you're free, right? Good.

12
00:01:00,708 --> 00:01:03,791
Meet us at 2:00 in front of
the station. And don't be late!

13
00:01:03,875 --> 00:01:07,000
[dial tone]

14
00:01:07,083 --> 00:01:09,750
[KYON] I didn't even have
a chance to say anything.

15
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:12,083
[phone rings]

16
00:01:12,166 --> 00:01:13,000
[KYON]
Now what?

17
00:01:13,083 --> 00:01:14,500
[HARUHI]
I forgot to tell you,

18
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:16,041
make sure to bring your swim
trunks and some money, too.

19
00:01:16,125 --> 00:01:19,333
Oh, wait, wait. And your bike.
Definitely bring your bike.

20
00:01:19,416 --> 00:01:21,166
That's it. Over and out!

21
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:23,333
--[dial tone]
--[KYON] Mhm.

22
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:24,541
That was weird.

23
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:26,375
It was like I knew what
Haruhi was gonna say

24
00:01:26,458 --> 00:01:28,125
before she even said anything.

25
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:30,291
Hang on... Actually,
it felt more like

26
00:01:30,375 --> 00:01:33,250
we'd had the exact same
conversation before,

27
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:35,208
like déjà vu or something.

28
00:01:35,291 --> 00:01:36,375
[COMMENTATOR]
And the pitch...

29
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:37,250
[metal clink]

30
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:38,416
[KYON'S SISTER gasps]

31
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:39,583
[COMMENTATOR]
It's a big, fat hit!

32
00:01:39,666 --> 00:01:41,458
[KYON]
Summer's almost over...

33
00:03:15,166 --> 00:03:16,541
[HARUHI]
You're late again, Kyon!

34
00:03:16,625 --> 00:03:18,458
Where is your motivation?

35
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,208
[KYON]
Yeah, yeah.

36
00:03:20,291 --> 00:03:22,125
I'm sorry to keep you waiting.

37
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:24,791
No worries. I just
got here, too.

38
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:27,000
[HARUHI] Now that we're all
present and accounted for,

39
00:03:27,083 --> 00:03:28,333
we can go!

40
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:29,625
Where to?

41
00:03:29,708 --> 00:03:31,791
To the public swimming pool!
Where do ya think?

42
00:03:31,875 --> 00:03:34,208
[KYON] That figures...
considering the stuff I brought.

43
00:03:34,291 --> 00:03:36,916
We've got lots and lots of
summer vacation-y things

44
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,541
to do during our summer break!

45
00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:40,333
But, we've only so
much time because

46
00:03:40,416 --> 00:03:42,291
once it's gone,
it's gone for good!

47
00:03:42,375 --> 00:03:44,708
So we're gonna do everything
we can, while we can

48
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:47,125
during our only summer
as tenth graders!

49
00:03:47,208 --> 00:03:50,208
And for starters, we're riding
the bikes to the pool!

50
00:03:50,291 --> 00:03:52,291
Okay. Did everyone
ride their bikes today?

51
00:03:52,375 --> 00:03:54,791
No... The only bikes
we have to ride over

52
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:56,375
are the ones you and I brought.

53
00:03:56,458 --> 00:03:57,416
[KYON]
Huh?

54
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:03,125
All right, Kyon! You can't
let Koizumi beat you!

55
00:04:03,208 --> 00:04:05,583
Come on! Full speed ahead!

56
00:04:05,666 --> 00:04:07,625
[KYON]
No ESP allowed!

57
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:11,041
[HARUHI] Come on, guys,
hurry up and park your bikes.

58
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:14,750
Kyon! We're trying to
have fun, so stop acting tired!

59
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,375
[KYON]
And whose fault is that?!

60
00:04:16,458 --> 00:04:18,875
[HARUHI]
Mmm, can you smell the chlorine?

61
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:21,125
That really makes
it feel like summer!

62
00:04:24,666 --> 00:04:26,375
[HARUHI gasps]
Hurry and get in!

63
00:04:26,458 --> 00:04:28,916
Come on, the water's warm!
It's perfect!

64
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,666
[KYON] Can't she see
the "no diving" signs?

65
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:31,833
They're everywhere!

66
00:04:31,916 --> 00:04:34,583
Well, that looks like fun.
Don't you think?

67
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:37,541
I mean, seeing her enjoy
the day in a normal fashion.

68
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:40,208
It's a rather
charming sight, isn't it?

69
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:43,500
And as long as Miss Suzumiya's
having a good time here,

70
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:46,625
we don't have to worry about
any earth-shattering events.

71
00:04:46,708 --> 00:04:48,083
[KYON]
I hope you're right.

72
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:51,041
[KYON]
What's wrong?

73
00:04:51,125 --> 00:04:52,708
Oh, nothing.

74
00:04:56,125 --> 00:04:58,208
It's probably my imagination.

75
00:04:58,291 --> 00:05:00,708
Come on, let's go and
have some fun, too.

76
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:21,541
[MIKURU giggles]

77
00:05:21,625 --> 00:05:23,375
[KYON] It's so bitter!
May I have another?

78
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:34,958
[KYON] That's weird. It's like
I've seen this before.

79
00:05:35,041 --> 00:05:38,208
Nagato... sitting all alone,
looking bored...

80
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:39,458
[HARUHI]
Kyon!

81
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:44,916
[KYON] Yeah... And then Haruhi
shows up, and she says...

82
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,416
So, these two guys are
my brigade members.

83
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,666
They do what I say.

84
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:50,750
So if you want something,
you can ask them!

85
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:51,958
Time for some fun!

86
00:05:52,041 --> 00:05:54,208
Let's play dodgeball
in the pool!

87
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:57,583
We're coming!

88
00:05:57,666 --> 00:06:01,041
[KYON] Oh, well.
Sometimes déjà vu's happen.

89
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:06,333
[HARUHI] I've been thinking of
some fun things we could do!

90
00:06:06,416 --> 00:06:07,708
Check it out!

91
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:09,041
[KYON]
What is that?

92
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:10,541
It's a schedule of
how we're gonna

93
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:12,791
spend the rest of
our summer vacation!

94
00:06:12,875 --> 00:06:14,375
I realized something...

95
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:17,958
We've only got two more weeks
of summer vacation left to go!

96
00:06:18,041 --> 00:06:20,208
That fact totally blew me away.

97
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:23,208
We've done a lot of cool things
but we've only got so much time,

98
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:26,000
and there's a bajillion
more things left to do!

99
00:06:26,083 --> 00:06:28,291
So I say, we gotta
pick up the pace!

100
00:06:28,375 --> 00:06:31,125
[KYON] We've got two
weeks to do all that?!

101
00:06:31,208 --> 00:06:33,333
Mikuru, is there anything
else you wanna do?

102
00:06:33,416 --> 00:06:34,666
[MIKURU]
Huh?

103
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:38,000
Um... I think I'd like to
try goldfish scooping?

104
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:41,333
[HARUHI] Okay!
Goldfish scooping, it is...

105
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:43,208
Could I see the list you made?

106
00:06:44,875 --> 00:06:45,833
[KOIZUMI]
Hm.

107
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,000
Okay, thanks.

108
00:06:49,083 --> 00:06:50,833
[HARUHI]
We'll start the list tomorrow!

109
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:53,750
Do you guys know if there's a
bon festival happening anywhere?

110
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,625
Or even a firework show?

111
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:58,958
I could check around for those.
I'll call you if I find one.

112
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:00,833
Don't forget about
goldfish scooping.

113
00:07:00,916 --> 00:07:03,583
After all, it's Mikuru's
only request.

114
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:05,833
[KOIZUMI]
Okay, I'll get right on it.

115
00:07:05,916 --> 00:07:08,291
That's it for today! See ya!

116
00:07:08,375 --> 00:07:09,791
I'll be going, too.

117
00:07:09,875 --> 00:07:11,458
[MIKURU]
Me too. Bye!

118
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:24,791
[KYON]
Nagato!

119
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:27,916
Hey, sorry, it's nothing
important or anything...

120
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,166
So, how have you been?
Is everything okay?

121
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,250
It is.

122
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:33,916
[KYON]
Oh! Good!

123
00:07:41,166 --> 00:07:43,291
[KYON]
What was that all about?

124
00:07:43,375 --> 00:07:45,333
Why'd I want to talk to her?

125
00:07:49,125 --> 00:07:51,375
[ANNOUNCER] May I have
your attention, please.

126
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:54,208
We have a lost child...

127
00:07:54,291 --> 00:07:55,750
[KYON]
A bon festival, huh?

128
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:57,416
Figures it'd be so crowded.

129
00:07:58,916 --> 00:07:59,875
[KYON gasps]

130
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:04,875
That tower... Those vendors...

131
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:06,791
I haven't been to a
bon festival in a while,

132
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:09,125
but it feels like I
just went to one.

133
00:08:09,208 --> 00:08:10,666
[HARUHI]
Mikuru!

134
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:12,875
They have goldfish scooping over
there, just like you wanted!

135
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:14,458
Come on, you're gonna
catch a ton!

136
00:08:14,541 --> 00:08:15,708
[MIKURU whimpering]
Okay...

137
00:08:15,791 --> 00:08:17,666
Do you wanna go
scoop some fish, too?

138
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:19,125
We could have a contest.

139
00:08:19,208 --> 00:08:20,500
Think I'll pass.

140
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:23,000
How 'bout you, Nagato?
You wanna go get some food?

141
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,791
[KYON] I didn't know you
were into this kinda stuff.

142
00:08:29,875 --> 00:08:30,500
I got it!

143
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:31,375
[NAGATO]
No.

144
00:08:31,458 --> 00:08:32,375
That one.

145
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:35,458
[VENDOR]
Sure, 800 yen!

146
00:08:35,541 --> 00:08:37,875
[KYON] I wish she would've
let me buy that for her...

147
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:41,750
It's the least I could do
after all she's done for us.

148
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,041
[HARUHI]
Thirteen fish!

149
00:08:43,125 --> 00:08:45,458
It's like the most
unbelievable haul ever!

150
00:08:45,541 --> 00:08:47,500
But, I don't have any
place to put 'em all.

151
00:08:47,583 --> 00:08:51,166
So I just kept one, and I
gave another one to Mikuru!

152
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:55,458
Go ahead and have one,
but only one!

153
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:57,458
[KYON]
Thanks.

154
00:08:57,541 --> 00:09:00,833
Hey, Yuki, what's up with
the mask you got there?

155
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:01,708
I bought it.

156
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:04,208
Oh... Okay.

157
00:09:04,291 --> 00:09:06,500
[giggles]

158
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:11,583
[sizzling]

159
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:20,916
[KYON] It was summer,
and summer vacation.

160
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,416
I guess that's why I
wanted to forget about it.

161
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:26,333
Truth was, I couldn't
ignore it any longer.

162
00:09:26,416 --> 00:09:28,583
Haruhi, I don't want
to spoil your fun,

163
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:30,458
but did you finish
your homework?

164
00:09:30,541 --> 00:09:31,666
Are you kidding?

165
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:33,208
That stuff's totally easy.

166
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:35,250
You can finish it
in like three days.

167
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:36,583
[KYON]
Three days?!

168
00:09:36,666 --> 00:09:38,208
[HARUHI] You have to
get rid of that junk first,

169
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:39,875
so you can spend the
rest of your summer

170
00:09:39,958 --> 00:09:41,916
having fun and not
worrying about it!

171
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:45,708
[KYON] Why does she
have to be so smart?

172
00:09:45,791 --> 00:09:47,625
The folks upstairs
weren't terribly fair

173
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:50,208
when they were divvying
up the stats for us.

174
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:53,041
You guys! Tomorrow,
we're gonna go catch some bugs!

175
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:54,208
And the prize for whoever

176
00:09:54,291 --> 00:09:56,250
catches the most
bugs is gonna be...

177
00:09:56,333 --> 00:10:00,083
...um... I know! They get to be
brigade leader for a whole day!

178
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:00,958
[KYON]
No thanks!

179
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:02,666
That sounds like a lot of fun!

180
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,541
Can we catch just
any random bug?

181
00:10:04,625 --> 00:10:07,541
Um... No... Only cicadas!

182
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:09,750
In fact, I'm calling it
the SOS Brigade's

183
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:12,208
cicada catching contest!

184
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:16,541
[KYON] The next day was
beautiful, sunny, and bright.

185
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,458
In fact, it was the
perfect day for us

186
00:10:18,541 --> 00:10:21,083
to have our SOS Brigade's
cicada catching contest.

187
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:22,791
[KYON yelling]

188
00:10:22,875 --> 00:10:23,916
[KYON]
That's not a cicada.

189
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,791
I-It's a yanbaru
long-armed scarab!

190
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:29,583
Although everyone caught bugs
the best way they knew how,

191
00:10:29,666 --> 00:10:31,458
the winner of the
contest ended up being...

192
00:10:31,541 --> 00:10:34,375
You guessed it, Haruhi.

193
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:36,166
It's important to
follow the spirit of

194
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:38,541
catch and release
with these guys.

195
00:10:38,625 --> 00:10:40,416
You never know,
if we let 'em go now,

196
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,916
they might come back
and return the favor!

197
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,375
[KYON] What could
a cicada do for me,

198
00:10:44,458 --> 00:10:46,250
even if it did come back?

199
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:50,666
[HARUHI] Hurry!
Go back to the mountains!

200
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:54,375
[cicada's chirping]

201
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:57,416
[KYON]
I sorta feel like Pandora,

202
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,458
when she opened her box.

203
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:03,250
[MIKURU]
Welcome to our store!

204
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:04,750
[KYON]
We met the next day,

205
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:07,750
even though we had absolutely
no idea what was going on.

206
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:08,958
Our confusion continued

207
00:11:09,041 --> 00:11:10,708
as we stood outside
the local supermarket,

208
00:11:10,791 --> 00:11:13,750
wearing frog costumes
and handing out balloons.

209
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,000
It's a living.

210
00:11:16,625 --> 00:11:19,416
[MIKURU whimpers]

211
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:22,791
I feel like Unit Zero after
it got hit by that beam.

212
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:25,250
Hey, guys! Awesome job today!

213
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:26,416
[KYON] What's with
the special treatment?!

214
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,791
You're the best!

215
00:11:27,875 --> 00:11:29,958
The manager's super grateful
for all the hard work.

216
00:11:30,041 --> 00:11:33,333
[KYON] Who cares how grateful
he is? What about our pay?

217
00:11:33,416 --> 00:11:34,500
There it is!

218
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:36,125
Huh?!

219
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:39,916
I've had my eye on this
little guy for a long time now.

220
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,500
--[giggles]
--[KYON] We worked in the sun,

221
00:11:41,583 --> 00:11:43,333
sweat pouring down
our foreheads...

222
00:11:43,416 --> 00:11:44,583
...for that?!

223
00:11:44,666 --> 00:11:46,500
We'll keep him in the
club room as a souvenir.

224
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:48,458
Oh, and Mikuru,
you have my permission

225
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:50,000
to wear him whenever you want.

226
00:11:50,083 --> 00:11:51,375
Help yourself, okay?

227
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:54,416
[MIKURU]
Sure! Uh...

228
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,625
[KYON]
Yeah? What?

229
00:11:55,708 --> 00:11:56,833
Oh, it's nothing.

230
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:57,500
[KYON]
Don't stare at me.

231
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:58,666
Come on, Mikuru!

232
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,458
You're the cutest
little froggy ever!

233
00:12:00,541 --> 00:12:02,208
Put it back on,
you know you want to!

234
00:12:02,291 --> 00:12:04,250
Watch the popsicle, ladies.

235
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,875
[phone rings]

236
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:09,250
[KYON]
Later that night,

237
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:12,083
my peaceful slumber was
interrupted by a phone call.

238
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:13,416
[KYON sighs]

239
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:14,916
[KYON] The number you have
dialed is no longer...

240
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,750
[MIKURU whimpers]

241
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:20,375
[KYON screams]
What the heck?!

242
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:21,416
[MIKURU whimpering]
Kyon...

243
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,250
Miss Asahina, is that you?

244
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,916
[MIKURU sobbing]
Yes... It's me...

245
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,583
Something... really bad...

246
00:12:28,666 --> 00:12:32,375
I don't know... Wha...

247
00:12:32,458 --> 00:12:33,333
What's wrong?

248
00:12:33,416 --> 00:12:35,375
[KOIZUMI]
Hello, it's Koizumi.

249
00:12:35,458 --> 00:12:36,875
How about you tell
me what you're doing

250
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:39,250
with Miss Asahina in
the middle of the night?

251
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:41,750
[KOIZUMI]
We have a situation here.

252
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:44,000
Would it be possible for
you to come meet us now?

253
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:54,000
Miss Asahina! Is everything
okay? What happened?

254
00:12:54,083 --> 00:12:55,333
[MIKURU sobbing]

255
00:12:55,416 --> 00:13:01,166
Oh, Kyon! I-I-I can't
go back to the future...!

256
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,166
[KOIZUMI]
I'll explain it the best I can.

257
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:10,375
Currently, we're stuck in a time
loop that seems to be infinite.

258
00:13:10,458 --> 00:13:11,666
[KYON] It's hard to
believe you're serious

259
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:14,500
with you sitting there,
smiling like that.

260
00:13:14,583 --> 00:13:15,875
I mean, come on, Koizumi.

261
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:18,041
Do you have any idea
what you just said?

262
00:13:18,125 --> 00:13:22,208
Yes, of course, I do. Much more
than I want to, believe me.

263
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,916
Earlier, I was having a
chat with Miss Asahina.

264
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,125
[KYON] Next time, you guys
are chatting, call me!

265
00:13:27,208 --> 00:13:29,416
And then suddenly, we came
to the conclusion that

266
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:32,750
there was something a little off
about the current flow of time.

267
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:36,041
But the truth is,
Miss Asahina discovered it.

268
00:13:36,125 --> 00:13:38,625
Thanks to her, my suspicions
were confirmed.

269
00:13:38,708 --> 00:13:40,291
What suspicions?

270
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:41,958
[KOIZUMI]
Hm.

271
00:13:42,041 --> 00:13:43,958
We're currently stuck
in a time loop,

272
00:13:44,041 --> 00:13:45,708
re-living the same
period of time,

273
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:47,041
over and over again.

274
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:48,958
[KYON]
Yeah, you already said that.

275
00:13:49,041 --> 00:13:50,791
[KOIZUMI] We've been
repeating every day between

276
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:54,458
August the 17th
through the 31st.

277
00:13:54,541 --> 00:13:56,166
We're in the middle
of what seems to be

278
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:58,583
an endless summer vacation.

279
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:01,333
Well, at least it's summer
vacation anyway...

280
00:14:01,416 --> 00:14:04,958
It's a never-ending,
endless summer vacation.

281
00:14:05,041 --> 00:14:08,041
The future doesn't exist
in this world anymore.

282
00:14:08,125 --> 00:14:10,791
Time stops at September the 1st.

283
00:14:10,875 --> 00:14:12,708
And who's gonna
believe such a thing?

284
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:14,625
Well, for starters,
we were sort of hoping that

285
00:14:14,708 --> 00:14:16,583
you would believe it.

286
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:17,750
[MIKURU]
Um...

287
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:21,083
I think I can try to explain it.

288
00:14:21,166 --> 00:14:22,583
Okay, here it goes...

289
00:14:22,666 --> 00:14:24,833
Because I have to
classified information,

290
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:29,458
I used classified information
to get in touch with the future.

291
00:14:29,541 --> 00:14:32,833
The thing is, I haven't gotten
any classified information

292
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:35,708
for about a week now.

293
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,708
And that's kind of weird.

294
00:14:37,791 --> 00:14:42,208
I was so surprised,
I classified information.

295
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:44,125
I really did.

296
00:14:44,208 --> 00:14:48,166
But it was classified
information.

297
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:51,041
I don't know what to do.

298
00:14:53,666 --> 00:14:55,041
[KYON]
What about those closed spaces

299
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:56,500
you were talking about before?

300
00:14:56,583 --> 00:14:58,166
Maybe we're trapped
in one of those.

301
00:14:58,250 --> 00:14:59,958
No, it's not one of those.

302
00:15:00,041 --> 00:15:03,250
A section of time has been
torn away from time-space.

303
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:07,583
At exactly midnight on August
the 31st, everything will reset.

304
00:15:07,666 --> 00:15:09,041
Then time reverts straight back

305
00:15:09,125 --> 00:15:11,125
to the morning of
August the 17th.

306
00:15:11,208 --> 00:15:12,833
That's the process.

307
00:15:12,916 --> 00:15:14,708
What about our-- No, wait.

308
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:16,750
What about the whole
world's memories?

309
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:18,666
Their memories are reset.

310
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:22,250
Everyone's memory starts
over from the beginning.

311
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:25,500
Perfect, another
problem involving time.

312
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:28,166
I guess that figures when
there's a time traveler around.

313
00:15:29,583 --> 00:15:32,666
No, Miss Asahina didn't
have anything to do with this.

314
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:35,375
[KYON]
Then, what's causing it?

315
00:15:35,458 --> 00:15:37,416
It's Miss Suzumiya.

316
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:38,458
[KYON sighs]

317
00:15:38,541 --> 00:15:40,125
I'm sure she doesn't
even realize it.

318
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:41,958
I think subconsciously,
she wants to

319
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:44,125
have summer vacation
last forever.

320
00:15:44,208 --> 00:15:45,500
You're kidding!

321
00:15:45,583 --> 00:15:47,541
You're telling me she still
hasn't had enough fun?

322
00:15:47,625 --> 00:15:49,583
Yeah, that's what I think.

323
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:51,083
[KYON sighs]

324
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:52,291
[KOIZUMI] Perhaps she feels
there's something else that

325
00:15:52,375 --> 00:15:54,291
needs to happen before
our summer vacation

326
00:15:54,375 --> 00:15:55,958
